k has been primarily a tourist performance. Drawing on over twenty years of fieldwork and meticulous archival study, Kendra Stepputat provides here a comprehensive study of the history, form, and cultural significance of the kecak. The first part of the book focuses on the kecak in its present form, including musical, choreographic, and dramatic elements. The connection between cultural tourism on Bali and kecak performance practice is analyzed in detail, including the dependency between tourism professionals and artists and ways of promoting the kecak. Tourists' perspectives on the kecak are addressed separately. The second part deals with the genesis and development of the kecak from the 1930s onward, exploring how it became and stayed a tourist genre for more than eighty years.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBalinese (Indonesian people)vMusic. 0aDancezIndonesiazBali Island. 0aHeritage tourismzIndonesiazBali Island. 0aKecak (Dance drama)xHistoryzIndonesiazBali Island. 0aMusiczIndonesiazBali Island. 4aModern History. 4aMusic. 7aMUSIC / Ethnomusicology.2bisacsh  aAfrican Tradition.  aBali.  aCultural Significance.  aCultural Tourism.  aDramatic Dance Performance.  aFieldwork.  aHistory.  aIndian Ramayana Epic.  aKecak.  aKendra Stepputat.  aLiving Scenery.  aMale and Female Solo Dancers.  aMusicians.  aTourist Performance.  aTourists' Perspectives.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311143100040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781800103092?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781800103092423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781800103092/original  a978-3-11-143100-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles